WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:29.029 --> 00:30.374
Babe, leave it!

00:30.398 --> 00:31.208
Let's go!

00:31.232 --> 00:32.566
We gotta go now!

00:41.109 --> 00:42.443
Mommy.

00:48.649 --> 00:50.194
It's not him, Faith.

00:50.218 --> 00:52.996
Don't leave me, Mommy, please.

00:53.020 --> 00:53.963
That's not our son.

00:53.987 --> 00:55.165
Oh God.

00:55.189 --> 00:56.900
I don't wanna be alone.

00:56.924 --> 00:58.326
Faith, come on.

01:04.565 --> 01:05.899
Mommy, please.

01:08.702 --> 01:09.537
Faith?

01:11.939 --> 01:12.949
No!

01:12.973 --> 01:14.418
Faith!

01:14.442 --> 01:15.276
Faith!

01:18.646 --> 01:19.480
No!

01:40.234 --> 01:42.446
I'm like 100% sure
we passed this road already.

01:42.470 --> 01:43.680
Are you sure you're not lost?

01:43.704 --> 01:45.515
No, I know where I'm going.

01:45.539 --> 01:47.751
Feels like we're in
the middle of nowhere.

01:47.775 --> 01:50.254
That's because we are in
the middle of nowhere, Hailey.

01:50.278 --> 01:52.256
Even if we were in
the middle of nowhere,

01:52.280 --> 01:55.225
which we're not by the
way, we're in it together,

01:55.249 --> 01:56.460
and that's what counts.

01:56.484 --> 01:57.318
Wow Dad.

01:58.486 --> 02:00.864
Well I for one
like the sentiment.

02:00.888 --> 02:03.567
It's a big move, but
we are in it together.

02:03.591 --> 02:05.869
Well yeah, just us and Shae.

02:05.893 --> 02:08.071
Hey, your aunt Shae
needs us right now.

02:08.095 --> 02:09.005
You never know.

02:09.029 --> 02:11.441
You might like living with her.

02:11.465 --> 02:14.978
Yeah, reformed
addicts are the best.

02:15.002 --> 02:15.836
Hailey.

02:19.240 --> 02:20.517
Listen, I know this is hard,

02:20.541 --> 02:22.051
but it's not forever.

02:22.075 --> 02:25.589
When the time is right, we'll
get our own place, I promise.

02:25.613 --> 02:28.091
Great, no service.

02:28.115 --> 02:29.726
I am in hell.

02:29.750 --> 02:31.661
Ah, give you some perspective.

02:31.685 --> 02:35.632
Really, because from my
perspective, I see trees.

02:35.656 --> 02:38.302
Oh oh look, another tree.

02:38.326 --> 02:40.261
Hah, look another tree.

02:42.129 --> 02:42.963
Oh wow.

02:59.413 --> 03:00.414
Toddy Bear!

03:01.482 --> 03:02.426
Oh I missed you.

03:02.450 --> 03:03.260
I missed you too.

03:03.284 --> 03:04.093
You look great!

03:04.117 --> 03:04.994
Thanks, so do you.

03:05.018 --> 03:05.829
You look amazing.

03:05.853 --> 03:06.763
Thank you.

03:06.787 --> 03:07.664
Hi Jess.

03:07.688 --> 03:08.598
Hi.

03:08.622 --> 03:11.034
You made it, I'm so happy.

03:11.058 --> 03:12.168
Hi Hailey.

03:12.192 --> 03:13.403
How's it goin'?

03:13.427 --> 03:14.371
You wearin' your
dad's clothes now?

03:14.395 --> 03:15.672
That's awesome.

03:15.696 --> 03:17.374
Welcome to the
not-so-big city, guys.

03:17.398 --> 03:19.443
Also known as the
smallest town ever.

03:19.467 --> 03:22.712
Yeah, we're quite far, far
away from pretty much anything.

03:22.736 --> 03:24.248
Yeah, at night
you're gonna love it.

03:24.272 --> 03:27.150
It's super zen underneath
the stars with the crickets.

03:27.174 --> 03:28.676
I hate crickets.

03:29.677 --> 03:31.412
Who hates crickets?

03:33.046 --> 03:34.524
I do?

03:34.548 --> 03:36.726
Come on, let's go, I wanna
show you inside the house.

03:36.750 --> 03:38.495
How many times do
you think she says zen?

03:38.519 --> 03:41.522
Don't start, remember, zen.

03:44.392 --> 03:46.960
Wow, home sweet home, ladies.

03:54.435 --> 03:55.936
It's really old.

03:57.771 --> 03:59.773
It's called Victorian.

04:06.480 --> 04:09.293
It's got nice cross-breezes.

04:09.317 --> 04:10.994
Let me show you upstairs.

04:11.018 --> 04:11.852
Come on.

04:13.253 --> 04:14.831
Ah!

04:14.855 --> 04:16.333
I knew it.

04:16.357 --> 04:17.500
All right guys, be really
careful with the railing.

04:17.524 --> 04:18.702
It's super delicate,

04:18.726 --> 04:22.262
and I broke one of them
by accident already.

04:23.664 --> 04:26.643
Okay, so each bedroom is like
painted totally different,

04:26.667 --> 04:29.045
like different kind of
wallpaper, different colors,

04:29.069 --> 04:30.471
it's really cool.

04:31.705 --> 04:33.040
This is my room.

04:34.475 --> 04:36.209
It's a mess, shocker.

04:38.446 --> 04:40.757
And then Hailey,
that's your room.

04:40.781 --> 04:43.050
Oh wow, flowers, awesome.

04:50.223 --> 04:51.401
Well this is your room now.

04:51.425 --> 04:54.571
So pick a color
and we'll paint it.

04:54.595 --> 04:55.905
Surrounding yourself by flowers

04:55.929 --> 04:58.141
is actually really
good for your chi.

04:58.165 --> 05:00.710
You should consider keepin' it.

05:00.734 --> 05:03.303
And this is the master bedroom.

05:04.505 --> 05:06.440
Oh this is beautiful.

05:12.880 --> 05:14.624
Okay, I'm gonna
check out the bathroom.

05:14.648 --> 05:15.983
See ya, sport.

05:17.050 --> 05:18.928
You did good.

05:18.952 --> 05:21.898
This house is just amazing.

05:21.922 --> 05:24.668
Yeah this is perfect
for us, yes, good job.

05:24.692 --> 05:26.403
I knew you guys would like it.

05:26.427 --> 05:28.195
I'll leave you to it.

05:32.065 --> 05:35.211
I just hope her and
Hailey can get along.

05:35.235 --> 05:37.781
I can definitely sense
something brewing there.

05:37.805 --> 05:39.849
No, no, they're
gonna get along fine.

05:39.873 --> 05:42.686
The problem is
they're so much alike.

05:42.710 --> 05:45.713
They're both rebels
without a cause.

05:48.449 --> 05:52.095
Okay I think for Hailey
it's called being a teenager.

05:52.119 --> 05:55.456
But for Shae, I don't
know what that is.

05:58.559 --> 06:01.638
You know, Shae's been
through a lot with Mom's death.

06:01.662 --> 06:05.875
But I think having family
nearby is going to be

06:05.899 --> 06:07.276
really good for her.

06:07.300 --> 06:08.135
I agree.

06:09.870 --> 06:14.484
And with this new job, we
can finally get back on track.

06:14.508 --> 06:16.844
Which I'm very grateful for.

06:18.145 --> 06:18.979
Me too.

06:23.851 --> 06:25.228
Todd, not now.

06:25.252 --> 06:26.362
What?

06:26.386 --> 06:27.230
Come on, it's okay.

06:27.254 --> 06:28.331
Hailey's outside.

06:28.355 --> 06:29.933
Your sister is downstairs.

06:29.957 --> 06:31.601
Shae does not care.

06:31.625 --> 06:32.436
Well it's weird.

06:32.460 --> 06:34.438
No it's not.

06:35.663 --> 06:38.231
Todd, no I'm not in the mood.

06:39.399 --> 06:41.902
You're never in the mood, Jess.

06:46.039 --> 06:46.874
I'm sorry.

06:47.841 --> 06:49.510
It was a long drive.

06:52.212 --> 06:53.881
I'm gonna go unpack.

07:05.025 --> 07:07.604
Hey, so how did you find this place?

07:07.628 --> 07:09.072
Just responded to an ad.

07:09.096 --> 07:10.273
The neighborhood
looked really nice,

07:10.297 --> 07:11.941
and the house was really cheap

07:11.965 --> 07:13.209
considering the
size of the place.

07:13.233 --> 07:14.444
So I jumped on it.

07:14.468 --> 07:15.879
I'm so surprised that
it was even available.

07:15.903 --> 07:17.905
This house is fantastic.

07:19.272 --> 07:20.684
My real estate
agent said something

07:20.708 --> 07:22.719
about the local
economy being down.

07:22.743 --> 07:23.653
People aren't moving.

07:23.677 --> 07:24.488
Makes sense.

07:24.512 --> 07:26.490
Well, their loss.

07:26.514 --> 07:27.924
I think this place is fantastic.

07:27.948 --> 07:30.951
And I absolutely
love the furniture.

07:32.285 --> 07:34.330
When I saw those
baroque couches,

07:34.354 --> 07:36.600
I was like where do I sign?

07:36.624 --> 07:38.067
Baroque.

07:38.091 --> 07:42.305
Did the family before here
leave their broke couch?

07:42.329 --> 07:43.430
I guess so.

07:44.665 --> 07:46.734
Nothing really matches.

07:47.701 --> 07:49.703
It's called character.

07:50.904 --> 07:52.148
Hey, do I have to go
to school right away?

07:52.172 --> 07:54.484
Hey, yes, you have to
go to school right away.

07:54.508 --> 07:57.020
Is there a specific reason
why you don't want to?

07:57.044 --> 07:58.688
Come on Dad, think about it.

07:58.712 --> 07:59.623
The semester's almost over.

07:59.647 --> 08:01.324
I can start next semester.

08:01.348 --> 08:04.894
I'll work extra hard, and
then it'll be a nice break.

08:04.918 --> 08:05.753
Please?

08:07.387 --> 08:08.221
Please?

08:12.926 --> 08:13.927
Seriously?

08:14.962 --> 08:18.474
You guys are way
too easy on her.

08:18.498 --> 08:20.009
Seriously Shae?

08:20.033 --> 08:21.945
You don't really
have a say here.

08:21.969 --> 08:23.212
Excuse me Hailey.

08:23.236 --> 08:25.782
You do not get to talk
to your aunt that way.

08:25.806 --> 08:28.484
I'm sorry, I'm not the
crazy drunk in the family.

08:28.508 --> 08:29.553
Hailey.

08:29.577 --> 08:30.820
Wow.

08:30.844 --> 08:32.087
I'm not gonna be the
one that's passed out

08:32.111 --> 08:33.322
in the front yard.

08:33.346 --> 08:34.823
Now you're just
being a little brat!

08:34.847 --> 08:35.991
You don't get to act like
you're such a good person

08:36.015 --> 08:38.962
just because you're
finally sober!

08:38.986 --> 08:39.886
Or are you?

08:41.688 --> 08:42.966
Great!

08:42.990 --> 08:44.391
This house sucks!

08:59.172 --> 08:59.973
Crickets.

09:42.750 --> 09:45.318
Wow, nice shot, sport.

09:48.922 --> 09:50.333
What's going on with you?

09:50.357 --> 09:51.835
What do you mean?

09:51.859 --> 09:54.437
I mean you were very rude
to your aunt Shae last night.

09:54.461 --> 09:55.371
It's not like you.

09:55.395 --> 09:56.773
Yeah, well she's a hypocrite.

09:56.797 --> 09:58.131
And I hate that.

09:59.232 --> 10:01.110
How is she a hypocrite?

10:01.134 --> 10:01.945
She tries to tell everyone else

10:01.969 --> 10:03.179
how to live their life.

10:03.203 --> 10:06.139
She can't even get
her own life right.

10:07.307 --> 10:09.886
I get that, but you
have to understand.

10:09.910 --> 10:11.420
Your aunt Shae, she's
been through a lot.

10:11.444 --> 10:12.689
We need to be patient
with her, help her.

10:12.713 --> 10:15.291
Isn't she supposed to
be able to help herself?

10:15.315 --> 10:17.260
Isn't that what rehab's for?

10:17.284 --> 10:20.287
Sweetheart, can
you do me a favor?

10:21.855 --> 10:23.066
What?

10:23.090 --> 10:23.967
Can you be the
bigger person here

10:23.991 --> 10:25.993
so we can all get along?

10:27.961 --> 10:29.797
It'd mean a lot to me.

10:30.998 --> 10:32.575
Okay.

10:32.599 --> 10:34.277
That's the Hailey I know.

10:34.301 --> 10:35.344
I gotta go to work.

10:35.368 --> 10:36.379
Bye, Dad.

10:36.403 --> 10:37.647
You're good right?

10:37.671 --> 10:38.939
Scouts honor.

12:42.395 --> 12:44.273
This town sucks.

12:44.297 --> 12:46.142
Let's go find some trees.

12:55.642 --> 12:56.476
Woo!

13:48.628 --> 13:51.040
Wow, that's a cool bike.

13:51.064 --> 13:52.565
It's a Yamaha 125.

13:53.533 --> 13:54.968
Yeah, you ride?

13:58.005 --> 13:59.815
No, I'm just a big motorhead.

13:59.839 --> 14:02.085
Sorry, who are you exactly?

14:02.109 --> 14:03.152
I'm Hailey.

14:03.176 --> 14:05.154
Who told you about this place?

14:05.178 --> 14:07.123
Nobody, I just heard the music.

14:07.147 --> 14:11.127
So you took that as an invitation.

14:11.151 --> 14:12.962
Do you like Higher Flux?

14:12.986 --> 14:15.298
Yeah, I actually
saw them in concert.

14:15.322 --> 14:16.399
I'm so jealous.

14:16.423 --> 14:18.367
What are you doing here?

14:18.391 --> 14:20.403
I just moved here to Amityville.

14:20.427 --> 14:23.039
Where in Amityville?

14:23.063 --> 14:26.166
On Amity, right
where it dead ends.

14:35.542 --> 14:38.121
So where'd you see them?

14:38.145 --> 14:39.488
See who?

14:39.512 --> 14:41.424
Higher Flux.

14:41.448 --> 14:42.282
Oh, L.A.

14:43.716 --> 14:44.627
Oh that's cool.

14:44.651 --> 14:45.895
Is that where you're from?

14:45.919 --> 14:48.431
No, I moved here
from San Francisco.

14:48.455 --> 14:50.190
Okay, well welcome.

14:55.195 --> 14:57.597
Yeah, I think I'm gonna go.

14:58.999 --> 15:00.843
Probably for the best.

15:00.867 --> 15:02.435
Nice to meet you.

15:03.770 --> 15:04.981
Yeah okay.

15:05.005 --> 15:07.716
I guess I'll just
see you around.

15:07.740 --> 15:09.142
See you around.

15:30.630 --> 15:32.841
Miss McCallister.

15:32.865 --> 15:34.801
Please, it's Delilah.

15:37.204 --> 15:38.038
Delilah.

15:40.507 --> 15:43.452
Oh, I guess you came for
the rest of the rent check.

15:43.476 --> 15:46.489
Sorry, I've been
painting all day.

15:46.513 --> 15:47.923
I'm really spaced out.

15:47.947 --> 15:48.948
An artist.

15:49.916 --> 15:52.419
It's more of a hobby really.

15:53.886 --> 15:57.066
Sorry I planned on dropping
this off to you later today.

15:57.090 --> 15:58.534
Hi.

15:58.558 --> 16:00.703
Oh, you must be Jessica.

16:00.727 --> 16:01.904
Jessica, this is Delilah.

16:01.928 --> 16:03.539
She's the property
manager on the house.

16:03.563 --> 16:04.664
Oh wow, hi.

16:05.898 --> 16:08.344
Just stopping by to
see how you're doing.

16:08.368 --> 16:10.213
We love the place.

16:10.237 --> 16:11.447
How's the garden?

16:11.471 --> 16:13.049
Oh, I've actually
never had one before.

16:13.073 --> 16:14.250
But the moment we moved in,

16:14.274 --> 16:15.484
I had the sudden urge
to just planting...

16:15.508 --> 16:16.719
Roses.

16:16.743 --> 16:17.686
Yes, exactly.

16:17.710 --> 16:18.654
I saw them outside.

16:18.678 --> 16:19.688
They're gorgeous.

16:19.712 --> 16:20.889
Thank you.

16:20.913 --> 16:22.058
Your husband and your daughter?

16:22.082 --> 16:23.226
Where are they, I would
love to meet them.

16:23.250 --> 16:25.261
Todd is at work, and Hailey,

16:25.285 --> 16:28.097
she's probably out
exploring or something.

16:28.121 --> 16:28.955
Pity.

16:34.494 --> 16:36.105
Do take care of the house.

16:36.129 --> 16:37.573
We will.

16:37.597 --> 16:40.867
Between you and I, it's
my favorite property.

16:42.602 --> 16:45.948
Oh, and don't let the
neighbors bother you.

16:45.972 --> 16:48.584
Why do they throw a
lot of crazy parties?

16:48.608 --> 16:50.319
No, they keep to themselves.

16:50.343 --> 16:52.321
You're just not gonna
make any friends.

16:52.345 --> 16:54.423
Oh, wow, that's all right.

16:54.447 --> 16:57.160
Well we have plenty of
drama in this family.

16:57.184 --> 16:59.962
Remember it's a small town.

16:59.986 --> 17:01.597
People like gossip.

17:01.621 --> 17:03.032
Don't you worry.

17:03.056 --> 17:06.969
What happens behind these
walls stays behind these walls.

17:06.992 --> 17:08.560
I'm sure it will.

17:22.409 --> 17:23.586
Hey.

17:23.609 --> 17:24.520
Hi.
Can I help you?

17:24.544 --> 17:25.753
Yeah I'm Todd Jacobson.

17:25.778 --> 17:26.954
I'm here to see Mike.

17:26.979 --> 17:27.890
Oh yeah, we've
been expecting you.

17:27.914 --> 17:29.158
Oh cool.

17:29.182 --> 17:29.825
Yeah I'm Karen,
nice to meet you.

17:29.849 --> 17:30.893
Hi Karen.

17:30.917 --> 17:32.419
Mike, Mike, hey.

17:34.654 --> 17:36.399
I got Todd here for you.

17:36.423 --> 17:37.233
What's up Mike?

17:37.257 --> 17:38.734
Hey Todd, Mike Arkos.

17:38.758 --> 17:40.436
Nice to finally meet you man.

17:40.460 --> 17:42.037
Glad to have you on board.

17:42.061 --> 17:43.005
Thank you.

17:43.029 --> 17:44.973
This is beautiful.

17:44.997 --> 17:45.841
What year is it?

17:45.865 --> 17:47.643
1955 Imperial.

17:47.667 --> 17:48.977
Fixing up for a friend of mine.

17:49.001 --> 17:50.045
She's a beauty, isn't she?

17:50.069 --> 17:51.680
Yeah, she's great.

17:51.704 --> 17:52.748
How is everything else going?

17:52.772 --> 17:53.582
Good man.

17:53.606 --> 17:54.950
Happy you're here.

17:54.974 --> 17:57.120
Now I can pay full
attention to the other shop.

17:57.144 --> 17:59.779
Come on, let me show you around.

18:14.561 --> 18:16.038
Jesus you scared me.
What?

18:16.062 --> 18:16.896
I'm sorry.

18:19.332 --> 18:21.644
Oh wow, who's your new friend?

18:21.668 --> 18:24.713
I found her while
I was planting roses.

18:24.737 --> 18:27.307
Well she is extremely creepy.

18:28.675 --> 18:29.585
She's not creepy.
No she's creepy.

18:29.609 --> 18:31.187
She's just old and dirty.

18:31.211 --> 18:32.721
Just like you.

18:35.182 --> 18:36.625
You know what, I
bet some little girl

18:36.649 --> 18:38.361
loved her very, very, very much.

18:38.385 --> 18:39.795
Oh no this isn't good.

18:39.819 --> 18:41.029
The problem with
these old houses,

18:41.053 --> 18:43.799
they have a big issue
with their plumbing.

18:43.823 --> 18:45.201
I'm gonna go check the basement

18:45.225 --> 18:46.769
for some drain cleaner.

18:46.793 --> 18:49.296
Have fun with your new friend.

18:53.566 --> 18:54.643
Hey Dad?

18:54.667 --> 18:55.668
Down here.

19:01.308 --> 19:03.819
This isn't ominous or anything.

19:03.843 --> 19:05.388
All basements
are ominous, honey.

19:05.412 --> 19:08.056
That's why they're
underneath the house,

19:08.080 --> 19:10.426
and not in the living room.

19:10.450 --> 19:12.861
So much junk down here.

19:12.885 --> 19:15.398
Who leaves this much
stuff when they move?

19:15.422 --> 19:16.599
I don't know,

19:16.623 --> 19:19.726
but it's basically
all cleaning supplies.

19:35.275 --> 19:36.108
Cool.

19:37.644 --> 19:38.887
Oh bingo.

19:41.648 --> 19:44.793
Everything's creep
about this house.

19:44.817 --> 19:46.486
Come on, let's go.

20:21.288 --> 20:22.731
Why is it that color?

20:22.755 --> 20:24.132
This is industrial strength.

20:24.156 --> 20:25.067
It's really potent.

20:25.091 --> 20:26.402
Actually stand back a bit there,

20:26.426 --> 20:27.370
because if this
gets on your skin,

20:27.394 --> 20:28.661
it'll burn you.

20:43.376 --> 20:44.720
Oh my God!

20:44.744 --> 20:46.255
Why does it smell like that?

20:46.279 --> 20:47.547
I don't know.

20:50.983 --> 20:53.252
Whoa, what's in this stuff?

21:27.454 --> 21:28.287
Shae?

21:35.362 --> 21:36.195
Shae?

21:37.897 --> 21:39.174
I can't get it open.

21:39.198 --> 21:40.367
Shae?

21:45.438 --> 21:46.382
Shae?

21:46.406 --> 21:48.708
Shae, open the door!

21:57.817 --> 22:00.396
Ah my skin is burning!

22:00.420 --> 22:01.630
I'm bleeding!

22:01.654 --> 22:03.332
Honey, I don't think
you're bleeding at all.

22:03.356 --> 22:04.400
It's probably just an acid trip.

22:04.424 --> 22:05.801
Not now, Hailey!

22:05.825 --> 22:08.070
I swear Todd, there is
something in the water.

22:08.094 --> 22:09.271
And it was burning me.

22:09.295 --> 22:10.373
It was burning my skin.

22:12.732 --> 22:14.242
The drain cleaner!

22:14.266 --> 22:15.478
You didn't check to see if
someone was taking a bath?

22:15.502 --> 22:16.645
Because that's not how
plumbing works, Jess.

22:16.669 --> 22:17.646
That's impossible.

22:17.670 --> 22:18.914
I couldn't get up.

22:18.938 --> 22:19.715
What are you talking about?

22:19.739 --> 22:21.007
I couldn't get up.

22:23.109 --> 22:24.653
Don't touch me!

22:24.677 --> 22:25.512
Get out!

22:29.982 --> 22:31.360
I told you, it
can't be connected.

22:31.384 --> 22:33.362
The drain cleaner,
it's impossible.

22:33.386 --> 22:35.631
What else was it, huh?

22:35.655 --> 22:36.889
I don't know.

22:42.228 --> 22:43.539
Maybe Hailey was right.

22:43.563 --> 22:46.208
Maybe she took something.

22:46.232 --> 22:47.543
Excuse me?

22:47.567 --> 22:48.444
Took something?

22:48.468 --> 22:49.277
Yeah, like...

22:49.301 --> 22:50.112
Oh great!

22:50.136 --> 22:51.580
Some acid or peyote.

22:51.604 --> 22:53.148
Great, we're
living with a junkie.

22:53.172 --> 22:55.217
You said she was
past all that, Todd!

22:55.241 --> 22:57.520
We're not living
with a junkie, Jess.

22:57.544 --> 22:58.987
I will keep an eye on her.

22:59.011 --> 23:00.456
It's not a problem.

23:00.480 --> 23:03.325
Listen, I get it,
she's your sister.

23:03.349 --> 23:05.528
But I have to make sure that you

23:05.552 --> 23:09.131
are not prioritizing your
sister over our daughter.

23:09.155 --> 23:11.299
Jess, I would never do that.

23:11.323 --> 23:12.668
Really, cause
you're doing it now.

23:12.692 --> 23:13.536
What does that mean?

23:13.560 --> 23:14.470
You gotta face it.

23:14.494 --> 23:15.538
Your sister's a drug addict.

23:15.562 --> 23:16.972
Our mother just died!

23:16.996 --> 23:20.275
She had one freak
out episode Jessica!

23:20.299 --> 23:21.744
Have a little compassion.

23:21.768 --> 23:22.678
Yeah, but you know what?

23:22.702 --> 23:23.946
The way you handled that episode

23:23.970 --> 23:24.947
seems like you've
done that before.

23:24.971 --> 23:25.881
How I handled it?

23:25.905 --> 23:26.815
