24:28.434 --> 24:32.147
It's just, you know with all
this creepy and craziness.

24:32.171 --> 24:33.616
Yeah, I know, I know, I know.

24:33.640 --> 24:37.486
This is not the first
episode that she has had.

24:37.510 --> 24:39.021
Why does it even happen?

24:39.045 --> 24:40.756
Honestly, I don't know.

24:40.780 --> 24:43.391
It could be stress, trauma,
you know Mom's death

24:43.415 --> 24:44.917
is a lot for Shae.

24:46.285 --> 24:47.262
Morning sunshine.

24:47.286 --> 24:48.454
Hi.

24:50.489 --> 24:52.568
Have I told you how
proud I am of you?

24:52.592 --> 24:53.502
Why?

24:53.526 --> 24:54.937
Why, because you're brave.

24:54.961 --> 24:56.905
You're going to a new school,
and that totally sucks.

24:56.929 --> 24:59.007
But you're doing it,
and I'm proud of you.

24:59.031 --> 24:59.942
At this point
I'll take any reason

24:59.966 --> 25:01.476
to get out of this house.

25:01.500 --> 25:03.779
Well, whatever motivates you.

25:03.803 --> 25:05.380
It doesn't mean I
wanna go to school.

25:05.404 --> 25:06.682
Look you don't have to wanna go.

25:06.706 --> 25:09.117
You just have to
do it, and you are.

25:09.141 --> 25:10.653
So I'm proud of you.

25:10.677 --> 25:12.721
Fine, I accept your pride.

25:12.745 --> 25:13.956
Oh thank God!

25:13.980 --> 25:16.024
