39:08.514 --> 39:10.692
I'm not hungry.

39:10.716 --> 39:11.550
Okay.

39:14.052 --> 39:15.997
Are you feelin' all right?

39:16.021 --> 39:17.856
Do I look all right?

39:19.791 --> 39:21.192
You look tired.

39:22.628 --> 39:24.939
Well I feel perfect.

39:24.963 --> 39:27.466
Wanna see what I'm working on?

39:28.867 --> 39:32.037
No, no I'll wait
'til it's finished.

39:54.826 --> 39:56.971
Well that was...

39:56.995 --> 39:58.163
Yeah it was.

40:00.466 --> 40:01.843
Oh I...

40:01.867 --> 40:02.701
Keep it.

40:03.902 --> 40:06.071
I'll get it the next time.

40:07.105 --> 40:10.384
Son, you know what time it is?

40:10.408 --> 40:12.319
Dad, I'm sorry.

40:12.343 --> 40:13.921
You're sorry, then you
know how late you are.

40:13.945 --> 40:15.213
Get inside now.

41:52.711 --> 41:54.989
What are you doing?

41:55.013 --> 41:56.057
Your door was open, so I just...

41:56.081 --> 41:57.415
Put that down.

42:03.789 --> 42:04.999
Do you like it?

42:05.023 --> 42:08.193
Yeah, I mean the
colors are amazing.

42:09.394 --> 42:11.462
I think you got a keeper.

42:17.135 --> 42:17.969
Okay.

42:22.173 --> 42:24.175
You know what I think?

42:26.978 --> 42:28.923
I think you're just a puppet

42:28.947 --> 42:31.392
that says whatever her
daddy wants her to say,

42:31.416 --> 42:34.028
'cause she doesn't have
a personality of her own.

42:34.052 --> 42:36.864
I think you act tough and cool

42:36.888 --> 42:41.059
so you can hide who you really
are, forgettable, unloveable.

42:42.327 --> 42:44.405
Why would you say that?

42:44.429 --> 42:47.098
'Cause the truth is important.

42:50.268 --> 42:54.716
I wish you would've died
instead of your brother.

42:54.740 --> 42:56.584
He only pretends to love you.

42:56.608 --> 42:58.085
Think about how happy
your father would be

42:58.109 --> 42:59.444
if he had a son.

43:31.843 --> 43:33.454
Hailey.

43:37.348 --> 43:39.284
Hailey, are you okay?

44:51.890 --> 44:52.991
Ow, damnit.

45:14.712 --> 45:15.546
Ah!

45:17.348 --> 45:19.226
Have you seen Todd?

45:19.250 --> 45:20.085
Todd!

45:21.219 --> 45:22.220
Fuck, gah!

45:38.303 --> 45:39.113
Oh shit!

45:39.137 --> 45:39.947
Todd!

45:39.971 --> 45:40.948
Stop the leak.

45:40.972 --> 45:41.783
Todd, stop now!

45:41.807 --> 45:43.184
Turn this thing off!

45:49.147 --> 45:50.724
Todd, stop that, turn it off!

45:50.748 --> 45:52.193
Todd, turn the welder off!

45:54.752 --> 45:56.087
Stop, stop Todd!

46:01.827 --> 46:03.494
Turn the welder off!

46:05.163 --> 46:05.997
Todd!

46:15.573 --> 46:16.407
Ahh!

46:44.502 --> 46:46.313
You want a cigarette, Failey?

46:46.337 --> 46:47.281
No.

46:47.305 --> 46:49.183
You gonna tell on us?

46:49.207 --> 46:53.787
Why would I stop you from
slowly killing yourselves?

46:53.811 --> 46:56.390
Nobody knows when
they're gonna die, Failey.

46:56.414 --> 46:58.960
I'd treasure this
moment if I were you.

46:58.984 --> 47:02.096
Yeah, tomorrow could be your last.

47:02.120 --> 47:03.597
Maybe not.

47:03.621 --> 47:05.199
I saw the way you looked
at my boyfriend, btdubs.

47:05.223 --> 47:06.733
Sorry who's your boyfriend?

47:06.757 --> 47:09.203
Oh I think you know.

47:09.227 --> 47:13.398
Watch your back, Failey, or
you'll find a knife in it.

47:19.170 --> 47:20.005
Ladies?

47:22.207 --> 47:23.550
Hailey.

47:23.574 --> 47:24.418
What are you doing?

47:24.442 --> 47:25.752
She slipped and fell.

47:25.776 --> 47:27.012
Classic Hailey.

47:30.415 --> 47:31.225
Hailey?

47:31.249 --> 47:32.350
Yeah, fine.

47:44.930 --> 47:46.540
He lived in my house.

47:46.564 --> 47:48.509
I know it because my aunt Shae

47:48.533 --> 47:51.445
found his medical
kit in her closet.

47:51.469 --> 47:53.180
And in the picture, his
daughter's holding the same

47:53.204 --> 47:56.683
doll that my mom found
buried in the garden.

47:56.707 --> 47:59.653
Okay, so he lived there.

47:59.677 --> 48:00.854
So what?

48:00.878 --> 48:03.424
So there's no record
of him since 2004.

48:03.448 --> 48:05.350
He doesn't exist Brett.

48:07.953 --> 48:08.786
He's dead.

48:11.222 --> 48:13.334
He died in my house.

48:13.358 --> 48:17.238
His family died in
my house, I know it.

48:17.262 --> 48:20.641
I can't prove it,
but I've seen him.

48:20.665 --> 48:22.109
And then there's this music box,

48:22.133 --> 48:25.036
and it plays at
really weird times.

48:26.271 --> 48:27.438
Like it knows.

48:32.510 --> 48:33.945
Do I sound crazy?

48:36.014 --> 48:37.949
No, I don't think so.

48:47.025 --> 48:50.071
I can't think
about this right now.

48:50.095 --> 48:53.198
Yeah that's fine,
we'll just chill.

49:22.227 --> 49:23.770
I haven't seen you
around here before.

49:23.794 --> 49:26.007
What's your name?

49:26.031 --> 49:27.241
Todd.

49:27.265 --> 49:30.201
Todd, you must not
live around here.

49:32.203 --> 49:33.380
Just drivin' through?

49:33.404 --> 49:35.349
No I live here.

49:35.373 --> 49:36.941
Hm, lucky for me.

49:41.646 --> 49:43.590
I'm married.

49:43.614 --> 49:44.682
Didn't ask.

49:46.584 --> 49:49.687
What about you,
your first concert?

49:51.489 --> 49:54.225
I have never been to a concert.

49:55.493 --> 49:56.770
No way.

49:56.794 --> 49:57.704
Are you serious?

49:57.728 --> 49:58.905
Yeah.

49:58.929 --> 50:02.500
Not a lot of bands come
through Amityville.

50:03.901 --> 50:04.735
Right.

50:09.340 --> 50:14.021
We should run away, escape
to civilization some time.

50:14.045 --> 50:15.646
Go see a concert?

50:17.014 --> 50:19.826
I actually wanna manage
my own band someday.

50:19.850 --> 50:24.021
Well, you know more about
what you wanna do than I do.

50:26.023 --> 50:29.070
My dad gets a lot
of credit for that.

50:29.094 --> 50:31.705
Taught me everything I know.

50:31.729 --> 50:35.900
How to be curious, ride a bike,
shoot arrows, play guitar.

50:38.035 --> 50:39.380
You play guitar too?

50:39.404 --> 50:40.414
You play guitar?

50:40.438 --> 50:41.248
Yeah!

50:41.272 --> 50:43.784
Yeah, that's awesome!

50:43.808 --> 50:44.651
Yeah um...

50:44.675 --> 50:46.287
We should jam.

50:46.311 --> 50:47.588
If I can remember how to play.

50:47.612 --> 50:50.848
My mom was teaching
me before she died.

50:52.950 --> 50:55.529
I didn't know your mom was dead.

50:55.553 --> 50:56.363
Yeah.

50:56.387 --> 50:57.331
Sorry.

50:57.355 --> 50:59.557
It happened when I was 13.

51:03.161 --> 51:05.772
I'm just glad that I got
the chance to know her.

51:05.796 --> 51:06.631
You know?

51:07.565 --> 51:08.399
Yeah.

51:11.702 --> 51:14.372
I actually had a little brother.

51:17.175 --> 51:19.786
But he died when I
was really little.

51:19.810 --> 51:21.379
He was just a baby.

51:22.547 --> 51:24.649
I didn't know him at all.

51:27.017 --> 51:28.853
You know it's funny.

51:31.322 --> 51:34.235
A lot of time when
people find out

51:34.259 --> 51:38.163
that I lost my mom, they
try to be sympathetic.

51:40.565 --> 51:41.775
But I know that
for the most part

51:41.799 --> 51:43.301
they don't get it.

51:45.770 --> 51:49.174
It's just nice to meet
somebody who does.

52:14.332 --> 52:15.833
Come on, let's go.

52:17.134 --> 52:18.745
Where?

52:18.769 --> 52:23.016
I think I might know
somebody who can help us.

52:33.684 --> 52:36.863
Hi Brett, I was expecting you.

52:36.887 --> 52:39.032
Wow, this is your room?

52:39.056 --> 52:40.334
It's cool right?

52:40.358 --> 52:42.503
Those are my solar crystals.

52:42.527 --> 52:45.739
These ones absorb positive
energy, those deflect evil.

52:45.763 --> 52:46.807
Deflect evil.

52:46.831 --> 52:48.709
Yeah, keep out the bad energy.

52:48.733 --> 52:50.444
What about that
one around your neck?

52:50.468 --> 52:53.046
You told me it was
really powerful.

52:53.070 --> 52:55.282
Yeah, it's an ancient
protection crystal.

52:55.306 --> 52:56.650
It's been passed down
for several generations

52:56.674 --> 52:57.951
in my family.

52:57.975 --> 52:59.420
Can't part with it.

52:59.444 --> 53:01.855
Well do you have anything
like that for Hailey?

53:01.879 --> 53:03.424
She just moved to a new
place in Amityville,

53:03.448 --> 53:05.683
and her aunt is kinda nuts.

53:06.884 --> 53:09.930
Yeah, I have lots of
stones for new houses.

53:09.954 --> 53:11.765
Hailey go into the bathroom
and grab the floral bag

53:11.789 --> 53:13.967
in the third drawer.

53:13.991 --> 53:14.892
Okay, I...

53:16.361 --> 53:19.364
It's the second
door on the right.

53:20.965 --> 53:23.143
What are you doing?

53:23.167 --> 53:24.611
What do you mean?

53:24.635 --> 53:26.780
That's the new girl that
just moved to the Amity house.

53:26.804 --> 53:28.014
Yeah, how did you...

53:28.038 --> 53:29.250
Word travels fast.

53:29.274 --> 53:30.884
Not to mention, Theresa
is not a fan of hers.

53:30.908 --> 53:33.454
Come on Jenny, she
really needs your help.

53:33.478 --> 53:34.755
Of course she needs my help.

53:34.779 --> 53:36.223
Everyone needs my help.

53:36.247 --> 53:37.891
But I can't get
involved in this.

53:37.915 --> 53:39.125
You have to go.

53:39.149 --> 53:41.218
Hey, Jenny, is this it?

53:42.387 --> 53:43.220
Exactly.

53:45.323 --> 53:46.833
This is bloodstone.

53:46.857 --> 53:50.194
It's known for its
protective qualities.

53:51.629 --> 53:54.040
I think I'm gonna need
somethin' a little bigger.

53:54.064 --> 53:55.876
It was nice to meet you Hailey.

53:55.900 --> 53:58.312
Thanks for coming over.

53:58.336 --> 53:59.970
See you later Brett?

54:13.384 --> 54:14.285
Hey baby.

54:17.021 --> 54:19.924
Why didn't you
answer your phone?

54:21.659 --> 54:24.995
I was here the whole
time, sweetheart.

54:34.238 --> 54:36.073
I killed Mike today.

54:40.044 --> 54:40.878
What?

54:45.149 --> 54:46.484
I killed Mike.

54:48.185 --> 54:50.120
What happened?

55:05.570 --> 55:07.572
There was an accident.

55:08.839 --> 55:10.841
Well accidents happen.

55:13.444 --> 55:14.779
Not like this.

55:15.946 --> 55:19.417
There was fire and it
just happened so quick.

55:23.220 --> 55:25.723
And I saw the look in his eyes

55:29.360 --> 55:30.628
right before he

55:32.997 --> 55:34.765
right before he died.

55:49.814 --> 55:52.817
I just wanna make
you feel better.

57:15.666 --> 57:17.902
Todd, is that you?

57:21.405 --> 57:22.239
Jess?

57:31.281 --> 57:33.951
I had the strangest day today.

57:36.020 --> 57:38.689
None of my roses wanted to live.

57:40.591 --> 57:42.827
Nothing wants to live here.

58:28.673 --> 58:29.506
Hey.

58:33.210 --> 58:34.044
Hey.

58:56.366 --> 58:57.811
Hey.

58:57.835 --> 59:00.947
If I get involved in
this and people find out,

59:00.971 --> 59:03.850
you know what's gonna happen.

59:03.874 --> 59:05.109
Yeah, I know.

59:06.510 --> 59:09.756
And there's no guarantee
it's gonna change the outcome.

59:09.780 --> 59:12.192
Nobody, I mean nobody can know.

59:12.216 --> 59:13.594
I get it.

59:13.618 --> 59:16.053
Look Hailey is a good person.

59:18.022 --> 59:20.090
She doesn't deserve this.

59:21.358 --> 59:23.469
I have an idea.

59:38.709 --> 59:39.543
Oh.

59:46.684 --> 59:47.928
That's the living room.

59:47.952 --> 59:49.930
Kitchen's down
back through there.

59:49.954 --> 59:51.832
And your bedroom?

59:51.856 --> 59:53.190
It's upstairs.

01:00:09.406 --> 01:00:10.307
This is it.

01:00:16.246 --> 01:00:20.093
So you gonna rid the house
of evil spirits or something?

01:00:20.117 --> 01:00:22.028
Can't get rid of the
evil, it's too powerful.

01:00:22.052 --> 01:00:24.965
The best thing I can do
is create a safe place.

01:00:24.989 --> 01:00:26.633
A safe place?

01:00:26.657 --> 01:00:29.369
Somewhere you can
go if things get bad.

01:00:29.393 --> 01:00:31.561
What do you mean by bad?

01:00:32.897 --> 01:00:33.998
I mean bad.

01:00:40.270 --> 01:00:41.715
What about my parents?

01:00:41.739 --> 01:00:42.983
You can bring them with you.

01:00:43.007 --> 01:00:45.385
This can be their
safe place too.

01:00:45.409 --> 01:00:46.720
I'm gonna put these
around the room.

01:00:46.744 --> 01:00:49.513
Whatever you do,
don't move them.

01:00:53.784 --> 01:00:55.228
Can I get some water?

01:00:55.252 --> 01:00:56.697
Yeah, yeah of course.

01:00:56.721 --> 01:00:58.322
I'll grab you some.

01:01:42.499 --> 01:01:44.168
Hey, how's it going?

01:01:45.469 --> 01:01:46.880
The spell's complete.

01:01:46.904 --> 01:01:48.839
I think you'll be okay.

01:01:55.946 --> 01:01:57.057
Jenny!

01:02:20.570 --> 01:02:22.015
Looks like someone
tried to help Failey

01:02:22.039 --> 01:02:23.616
bite off more than she can chew.

01:02:46.463 --> 01:02:48.108
♪ You heard the
whispers and the rumors

01:02:48.132 --> 01:02:49.742
♪ When you rolled into town

01:02:49.766 --> 01:02:52.245
♪ You felt the evil
in the air outside

01:02:52.269 --> 01:02:53.814
♪ swirlin' round and round

01:02:53.838 --> 01:02:57.517
♪ I'm all emaciated glad you
made it through the front door

01:02:57.541 --> 01:03:01.254
♪ But chances are you might
not like what's in store

01:03:01.278 --> 01:03:04.991
♪ Pay no attention to the
voices you hear beyond the walls

01:03:05.015 --> 01:03:08.962
♪ Those iridescent
nasty windbag in your woo

01:03:08.986 --> 01:03:12.665
♪ And you don't wanna
see this other side of me

01:03:12.689 --> 01:03:17.170
♪ But can you see me
from a new point of view

01:03:17.194 --> 01:03:19.139
♪ See delusions and Deja vu

01:03:21.131 --> 01:03:24.845
♪ Feels all broken and insulting

01:03:24.869 --> 01:03:28.681
♪ Feel wear it like a tattoo

01:03:28.705 --> 01:03:32.877
♪ Feel like magic and voodoo

01:03:55.232 --> 01:03:56.442
Hello.

01:03:56.466 --> 01:03:59.212
Hi, I'm looking
for David Cranston.

01:03:59.236 --> 01:04:00.713
Speaking.

01:04:00.737 --> 01:04:03.884
Awesome, I was actually
calling about your brother,

01:04:03.908 --> 01:04:05.585
Willis Cranston.

01:04:05.609 --> 01:04:06.776
Who is this?

01:04:07.912 --> 01:04:09.089
I actually moved into the house

01:04:09.113 --> 01:04:10.756
I think your brother
used to live in.

01:04:10.780 --> 01:04:12.525
I found some of his
surgical supplies,

01:04:12.549 --> 01:04:15.996
and I wanted to return them to...

01:04:16.020 --> 01:04:17.864
Well that's very kind of you.

01:04:17.888 --> 01:04:21.467
But we haven't heard from
Willis for over a decade now.

01:04:21.491 --> 01:04:23.569
Would you mind if
I ask what happened?

01:04:23.593 --> 01:04:25.071
I wish I knew.

01:04:25.095 --> 01:04:27.673
Once he moved to Amityville,
we never heard from him again.

01:04:27.697 --> 01:04:30.843
I contacted the police who
said that the property manager

01:04:30.867 --> 01:04:34.314
said that they'd handed in
the notice and moved on.

01:04:34.338 --> 01:04:35.949
To be honest it
was very strange.

01:04:35.973 --> 01:04:38.618
He would never just have
left without telling me.

01:04:38.642 --> 01:04:40.810
It doesn't make any sense.

01:04:41.979 --> 01:04:45.549
Who was the property
manager at the time?

01:04:47.251 --> 01:04:50.187
McCallister,
Delilah McCallister.

01:07:11.261 --> 01:07:12.262
Well well.

01:07:13.530 --> 01:07:16.766
Honey, you know
trespassing is illegal.

01:07:19.669 --> 01:07:21.238
Put the files down.

01:07:25.609 --> 01:07:28.712
I will cut out your
heart and eat it.

01:08:31.941 --> 01:08:34.120
How does somebody just
fall out of a closed window?

01:08:34.144 --> 01:08:35.821
I don't know, Jess.

01:08:35.845 --> 01:08:38.258
And our neighbors just stood
around like nothing happened?

01:08:38.282 --> 01:08:39.759
Hailey?

01:08:39.783 --> 01:08:42.094
Dad, Dad I just went to
Delilah McCallister's house

01:08:42.118 --> 01:08:45.531
and I found all of this
information about past renters.

01:08:45.555 --> 01:08:46.732
There's been hundreds.

01:08:46.756 --> 01:08:48.167
Dad, hundreds!

01:08:48.192 --> 01:08:49.100
Okay Hailey, slow down.

01:08:49.125 --> 01:08:50.270
What are you talking about?

01:08:50.294 --> 01:08:51.737
Since the '70s,
people have been moving

01:08:51.761 --> 01:08:53.139
in and out of our house.

01:08:53.162 --> 01:08:56.142
They never stay longer
than three months.

01:08:56.166 --> 01:08:58.578
I'm willing to bet
they're all missing.

01:08:58.602 --> 01:08:59.812
Okay Hailey, this is crazy.

01:08:59.836 --> 01:09:01.080
Why don't you just
come home and...

01:09:01.104 --> 01:09:02.715
Dad, you need to
get Mom and Shae,

01:09:02.738 --> 01:09:04.149
and you need to get
out of the house.

01:09:04.174 --> 01:09:05.885
Okay, I'm at the police station.

01:09:07.010 --> 01:09:09.189
Hailey, Hailey?

01:09:09.212 --> 01:09:10.046
Lost her.

01:09:10.913 --> 01:09:12.158
Dad?

01:09:12.182 --> 01:09:13.626
Dad?

01:09:13.649 --> 01:09:15.928
I just, I don't think that
we should be here anymore Todd.

01:09:15.952 --> 01:09:17.162
I'm serious.

01:09:17.187 --> 01:09:18.398
We're gonna wait for
Hailey to come home.

01:09:18.421 --> 01:09:19.499
We will leave first
thing in the morning.

01:09:19.523 --> 01:09:21.066
I'm gonna go talk to Shae okay?

01:09:21.090 --> 01:09:23.260
I'm gonna start packing.

01:09:32.902 --> 01:09:33.712
Hey.

01:09:33.737 --> 01:09:34.779
Brett?

01:09:34.804 --> 01:09:36.482
Oh thank God, are you okay?

01:09:36.506 --> 01:09:37.841
Yeah I'm fine.

01:09:38.808 --> 01:09:40.953
I heard about Jenny.

01:09:40.977 --> 01:09:42.888
Look I am so sorry.

01:09:42.912 --> 01:09:46.125
Brett I think I know what's
happening with my house.

01:09:46.149 --> 01:09:47.393
Hailey hold on.

01:09:47.417 --> 01:09:48.728
Delilah is moving people in there

01:09:48.752 --> 01:09:49.694
and killing them.

01:09:49.719 --> 01:09:51.287
It's not Delilah.

01:09:52.356 --> 01:09:54.189
I mean it is, kind of.

01:09:55.592 --> 01:09:58.971
Do you remember what I told
you about Jimmy Oberest?

01:09:58.995 --> 01:10:01.807
Yeah he drowned his
sister in a bathtub

01:10:01.831 --> 01:10:03.676
with acid and killed his family.

01:10:03.700 --> 01:10:07.871
Hailey, Jimmy and his entire
family were into black magic.

01:10:11.040 --> 01:10:14.854
They believed if they made
these human sacrifices

01:10:14.878 --> 01:10:17.189
that they'd be
granted eternal life.

01:10:17.213 --> 01:10:18.791
They killed people.

01:10:18.815 --> 01:10:20.216
Lots of people.

01:10:21.785 --> 01:10:23.829
Whatever they did, it was like

01:10:23.853 --> 01:10:27.066
they opened a portal
to hell or something.

01:10:27.090 --> 01:10:29.134
What's Delilah's connection?

01:10:29.158 --> 01:10:32.572
Delilah was Jimmy's baby sister.

01:10:32.596 --> 01:10:34.139
What?

01:10:34.163 --> 01:10:35.741
Not the one he drowned.

01:10:35.765 --> 01:10:37.209
She had pneumonia.

01:10:37.233 --> 01:10:39.745
She was in a hospital during
the time of the murders.

01:10:39.769 --> 01:10:42.282
Oh my God, I'm at
the police station.

01:10:42.306 --> 01:10:45.385
And they're putting
Jenny's body in a trunk.

01:10:45.409 --> 01:10:46.719
Look there's so much more.

01:10:46.743 --> 01:10:48.053
I need to tell you in person.

01:10:48.077 --> 01:10:49.322
